Docs.summary: Defines constants for Uniform Type Identifiers (UTIs) which are strings that identify a given class of type or item.

remarks.para: Uniform Type Identifiers (UTIs) are Apple's method for identifying data types.
UTIs use a reverse-DNS naming structure. Â UTIs support multiple inheritance, allowing files to be identified with any number of relevant types, as appropriate to the contained data.
